{
  "stem": "27770.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I should know the difference between waage and a wagon.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You understand?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So that's what happened.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this-- this Professor Epstein, when Mengele had no time to make a selection, he had to make the selection.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, the four crematoriums had to burn 24 hours.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was a sonderkommando.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If you ever heard about the sonderkommando, every six months, when we came a new transport, they took-- made a big, on the lautsprecher, on the microphone, doctors, engineers, intelligent people, dentists.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And everybody, of course, was there to say, yes, I am.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They took between 500 and 600 people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they made the job when they came out from the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had to pull them out from the gas chamber-- they were already naked, anyway-- and put in this crematorium.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "A crematorium oven, you couldn't go in more than 25 person at once.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "As they say, the way I heard-- I saw, later, the crematorium-- it took about 20 minutes to burn the body.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Of course, there was leftover bones, whatever.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But-- so their work was, day and night, to feed the crematorium with bodies.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And two doctors, who are from my hometown, Dr.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Havash and Dr.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Peter, when they was working, daytime, in the crematorium-- I mean, the nighttime-- daytime they came and they was cutting the grass.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So I was next to them and had a right to talk to one of the doctors.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they told me all the stories what was going on.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now they also told me what happened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In the gas chamber was officially room for 1,500 people to be gassed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But because they were afraid that the Russian were coming closer, they pushed 1,800 and sometimes 2,000 people in the same gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
